fields.value: Levels of C-reactive protein, creatine kinase-muscle and aldolase A are suitable biomarkers for detecting risk factors for osteoarthritic disorders: A novel diagnostic protocol

dsDescriptionValue.value: The present study deals with the evaluation of the levels of biochemical markers such as CRP, CK-MM, and AldoA and determine their correlations with risk factors for OADs. Baseline data from 297 patients with OADs and 315 participants without OADs aged 40 to 80 years old were collected in this cross-sectional study.
